parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot engine liquids to leak out, resulting in injuries to the driver and passengers, and potentially leading to engine overheating, which can cause further damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Hot engine liquids leaking onto the driver's legs

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked or broken seatbelt buckle can lead to a failure to properly restrain occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle is cracked or broken
the buckle does not latch or unlatch properly
the buckle fails to hold the seatbelt in place
the seatbelt becomes detached while in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rough shift into third gear can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the transmission.
symptoms: The transmission shifts roughly into third gear
especially when the engine is cold
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting into third gear
the transmission slips or hesitates before engaging third gear.
